"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-news-dublin-2024-0117-1427152-teen-olympian\", \"text\": \"  A Leaving Certificate student from Co Dublin is taking a break from her studies - to hurtle down the luge track for Team Ireland at the Winter Youth Olympic Games in South Korea.  Sixteen-year-old Lily Cooke from Baldoyle is one of four Irish athletes at the Games and the first to represent Ireland in the luge at this level.  Lily only took up the sport a little over a year ago but she is already making speedy progress.  Watch our video to hear more about her Olympic adventure.  \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026. RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media. RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.  Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\"}"